‚’ãƒã‚§ãƒƒã‚¯ã—ã¦ã¿ã¦ãã ã•ã„ã€‚\n\nãƒ¡ãƒ¼ãƒ«ã‚¢ãƒ‰ãƒ¬ã‚¹ã‚’ç™»éŒ²ï¼ˆJOIN THE LISTï¼‰ã—ã¦ãŠãã¨ã€ãƒã‚±ãƒƒãƒˆã®å…ˆè¡Œæƒ…å ±ãªã©ãŒå±Šãã¾ã™ã€‚\n\n### â–¼å…¬å¼ã‚µã‚¤ãƒˆã¯ã“ã¡ã‚‰\n\n**[https://solun.art/](https://solun.art/)**\n\nãƒ‰ãƒ¡ã‚¤ãƒ³ã‚‚ã€Œ.artã€ã€‚å˜ãªã‚‹ã‚¤ãƒ™ãƒ³ãƒˆã§ã¯ãªãã€ã‚¢ãƒ¼ãƒˆãªä½“é¨“ã‚’å‰µã‚Šä¸Šã’ã‚‹ã¨ã„ã†åƒ•ãŸã¡ã®æ„æ€è¡¨ç¤ºã§ã™ã€‚\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ¤ ã‚¹ãƒãƒ³ã‚µãƒ¼æ§˜ã‚‚å‹Ÿé›†ã—ã¦ã„ã¾ã™\n\næœ€å¾Œã«ã€ã“ã®æ–°ã—ã„æŒ‘æˆ¦ã€ŒSOLUNAã€ã‚’ä¸€ç·’ã«ç››ã‚Šä¸Šã’ã¦ãã ã•ã‚‹ã‚¹ãƒãƒ³ã‚µãƒ¼æ§˜ã‚‚å‹Ÿé›†ã—ã¦ãŠã‚Šã¾ã™ã€‚\n\nä¸–ç•ŒãŒæ³¨ç›®ã™ã‚‹ã“ã®ãƒ ãƒ¼ãƒ–ãƒ¡ãƒ³ãƒˆã«ã€ãã—ã¦æ—¥æœ¬ã¨ãƒãƒ¯ã‚¤ã‚’ç¹‹ãæ–°ã—ã„ã‚«ãƒ«ãƒãƒ£ãƒ¼ã®å‰µå‡ºã«ã€ãœã²åŠ›ã‚’è²¸ã—ã¦ãã ã•ã„ã€‚\n\n**9æœˆã€ãƒãƒ¯ã‚¤ã§ãŠä¼šã„ã§ãã‚‹ã®ã‚’æ¥½ã—ã¿ã«ã—ã¦ã„ã¾ã™ï¼**\n\n---\n\n## ğŸµ I Need Your Attention (Afro House Edition)\n\nã“ã®è¨˜äº‹ã‚’æ›¸ã„ã¦ã„ã‚‹ç­†è€…YukiãŒä½œæ›²ã—ãŸæ¥½æ›²ã€ŒI Need Your Attentionã€ã®Afro Houseãƒãƒ¼ã‚¸ãƒ§ãƒ³ã§ã™ã€‚SOLUNAã®ä¸–ç•Œè¦³ã«ã´ã£ãŸã‚Šã®ãƒ“ãƒ¼ãƒˆã‚’ãŠæ¥½ã—ã¿ãã ã•ã„ã€‚\n\nã“ã®æ›²ã¯ã€2017å¹´ã«Googleã®ç ”ç©¶è€…ãŸã¡ãŒç™ºè¡¨ã—ãŸæ­´å²çš„ãªè«–æ–‡ **ã€ŒAttention Is All You Needã€** ã«ã‚¤ãƒ³ã‚¹ãƒ‘ã‚¤ã‚¢ã•ã‚Œã¦ã„ã¾ã™ã€‚ã“ã®è«–æ–‡ã¯ã€ç¾ä»£ã®AIï¼ˆGPT-4ã€Claudeã€Geminiãªã©ï¼‰ã‚’æ”¯ãˆã‚‹Transformerã‚¢ãƒ¼ã‚­ãƒ†ã‚¯ãƒãƒ£ã‚’ä¸–ç•Œã«ç´¹ä»‹ã—ã€AIã®æ­´å²ã‚’å¡—ã‚Šæ›¿ãˆã¾ã—ãŸã€‚\n\nè«–æ–‡ã‚¿ã‚¤ãƒˆãƒ«è‡ªä½“ãŒãƒ“ãƒ¼ãƒˆãƒ«ã‚ºã®ã€ŒAll You Need Is Loveã€ã®ã‚ªãƒãƒ¼ã‚¸ãƒ¥ã§ã‚ã‚‹ã“ã¨ã‹ã‚‰ã€Yukiã¯ã“ã®æŠ€è¡“çš„ãªã‚³ãƒ³ã‚»ãƒ—ãƒˆã‚’æ‹æ„›ã®æ­Œè©ã«æ˜‡è¯ã•ã›ã¾ã—ãŸã€‚ã€Œã‚ãªãŸã®æ³¨ç›®ï¼ˆAttentionï¼‰ãŒå¿…è¦ã€ã¨ã„ã†ãƒ¡ãƒƒã‚»ãƒ¼ã‚¸ã¯ã€AIã®è‡ªå·±æ³¨æ„æ©Ÿæ§‹ï¼ˆSelf-Attentionï¼‰ã¨ã€äººé–“ã®æ„›æƒ…ã¸ã®æ¸‡æœ›ã‚’äºŒé‡ã«è¡¨ç¾ã—ã¦ã„ã¾ã™ã€‚\n\n[play:i-need-your-attention-afro]',
content_en = E'![ZAMNA HONOLULU - HAWAII](/images/blog-zamna-hawaii-ogp.png)\n\n## Hello everyone!\n\nToday, I want to share something that has me trembling with excitementâ€”a major project I''ve been preparing for.\n\nThe time has finally come to make this announcement.\n\n**ZAMNA**, the legendary mega-event that has captivated music fans worldwide in Tulum, Mexico, is **coming to Hawaii this September!**\n\nWe''ve officially secured the license for Japan and Hawaii, starting with Hawaii first.\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ¤ How I Ended Up on the Organizer Side\n\nHonestly, I never imagined I''d be involved in organizing an event this big.\n\nIt all started through my friend **Sean**. About two years ago, things started moving behind the scenes, gradually taking shape.\n\nI''m still very much a newcomer to the festival world. My experience is far from deep.\n\nBut here''s the thingâ€”**festivals are incredibly fun**.\n\nThat''s why I want to create something where anyone can come and have an amazing time. That''s my number one priority.\n\n---\n\n<video controls autoplay muted loop playsinline class="w-full rounded-xl my-8">\n  <source src="/videos/zamna-goes-to-hawaii.mp4" type="video/mp4">\n</video>\n\n## ğŸŒ´ What is ZAMNA - The Hottest Event in the World Right Now?\n\nIf you''re into music, you''ve probably heard about Tulum lately.\n\nSet in Mexico''s mystical jungles and cenotes (underground lakes), this is where ZAMNA takes place.\n\nIt rivals the world''s biggest EDM festivals like Tomorrowlandâ€”in fact, it''s now known as **"the hardest ticket to get in America."**\n\nMiami, Barcelona, Dubai... celebrities and music lovers worldwide are traveling just to experience this.\n\n---\n\n## ğŸµ Grammy Winner Black Coffee and the Magic of Afro House\n\nWhile called an "EDM event," the music at ZAMNA differs from typical flashy EDM or hardcore techno.\n\nThe centerpiece is **Afro House**.\n\nHave you heard of **Black Coffee**, the Grammy-winning DJ who symbolizes this genre? As he rose to global stardom, Afro House exploded in popularity.\n\nThe tempo is around BPM 120â€”slightly relaxed.\n\nRather than jumping and raving, it''s about immersive comfort between "chill" and "dance."\n\nSurrendering to rhythms close to your heartbeatâ€”this is **"premium electronic music for adults."**\n\nThe more I researched, the more I fell in love with its depth and the passionate following it commands.\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ‡³ğŸ‡± Amsterdam Dance Event and the Birth of SOLUNA\n\nLast year, I attended **ADE (Amsterdam Dance Event)**, the world''s largest music business conference in the Netherlands.\n\nSurrounded by music industry leaders worldwide, I absorbed cutting-edge trends, learned, and built connections.\n\nMy conviction grew: **"I want to create this incredible experience with my own hands."**\n\nThis isn''t just about bringing ZAMNA over.\n\nWe''re launching as **"ZAMNA HAWAII - Powered by SOLUNA"**.\n\n**SOLUNA** is our new brand.\n\n**SOL (Sun) and LUNA (Moon).**\n\nStarting under Hawaii''s sun, dancing under the moon. It symbolizes becoming one with nature.\n\nBeyond the ZAMNA collaboration, we envision growing SOLUNA as its own IP, expanding to Japan and the world.\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ”Š AI Audio Experiment â€” OpenSonic\n\nThere''s actually something else I''m working on for SOLUNA.\n\nAn **AI-powered audio system**.\n\nHonestly, I''m not sure if it''ll be ready by the event. But I believe the custom software I''m developing could enable some truly unique sonic experiences that haven''t existed before.\n\nHow far we can take it is still unknown, but stay tuned.\n\nThe source code is open. It''s simple, but if you take a look, you''ll get a sense of what we''re trying to do. It''s been a genuinely fun project to build.\n\n**ğŸ‘‰ [OpenSonic - GitHub](https://github.com/yukihamada/opensonic)**\n\n---\n\n## ğŸŒº September in Hawaii''s Great Outdoors - History in the Making\n\nThe dates are **September 4th (Friday) weekend** this year.\n\nThis coincides with **Labor Day Weekend**, the perfect timing when discerning people gather from across America.\n\nThe venue is **Hawaii Country Club**, away from Waikiki''s bustle.\n\nVast golf course greens and open-air natureâ€”a location reminiscent of Tulum''s jungles.\n\n**This event is set to become the largest outdoor music event in Hawaii''s history.**\n\n![SOLUNA presents ZAMNA HAWAII](/images/blog-soluna-logo.png)\n\nFeeling Hawaii''s breeze while losing yourself in incredible music... this will undoubtedly be a new experience Hawaii has never seen.\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ« Tickets & Pre-Registration\n\nOur official website is now live.\n\nFull promotions are coming, but given the global trend, tickets are expected to be in high demand.\n\nIf you want to experience the cutting edge of what''s trending, or seek healing through comfortable music and Hawaiian air, please check out our official site.\n\nRegister your email (JOIN THE LIST) to receive early ticket information.\n\n### â–¼ Official Website\n\n**[https://solun.art/](https://solun.art/)**\n\nThe ".art" domain reflects our commitmentâ€”this isn''t just an event, it''s an artistic experience.\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ¤ Sponsors Wanted\n\nFinally, we''re seeking sponsors to help energize this new venture, SOLUNA.\n\nJoin us in this globally-watched movement and help create new culture connecting Japan and Hawaii.\n\n**See you in Hawaii this September!**\n\n---\n\n## ğŸµ I Need Your Attention (Afro House Edition)\n\nThis is the Afro House version of "I Need Your Attention," composed by Yuki, the author of this article. Enjoy the beats that perfectly match the SOLUNA vibe.\n\nThis song is inspired by the historic paper **"Attention Is All You Need"** published by Google researchers in 2017. This paper introduced the Transformer architecture that powers modern AI systems like GPT-4, Claude, and Gemini, revolutionizing the field of artificial intelligence.\n\nSince the paper title itself is an homage to the Beatles'' "All You Need Is Love," Yuki transformed this technical concept into love song lyrics. The message "I need your attention" is a dual expression of AI''s self-attention mechanism and human longing for love.\n\n[play:i-need-your-attention-afro]',
